    "units": [
        {
            "id": "unit-dm-01",
            "title": "Module 1: SEO & Content",
            "order": 1,
            "slides": [
                {
                    "id": "dm-s01",
                    "order": 1,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "What is SEO?",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</h2><p>SEO is the practice of optimizing your website so it ranks higher in search engine results, driving <strong>organic (free) traffic</strong>.</p><div style=\"background:#dbeafe;padding:1rem;border-radius:8px;border-left:4px solid #2563eb\"><p>💡 <strong>Fact:</strong> The #1 result on Google gets ~28% of all clicks. Position #2 gets ~15%.</p></div><p>Two main areas: <strong>On-page SEO</strong> (your content) and <strong>Off-page SEO</strong> (external links).</p>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "dm-s02",
                    "order": 2,
                    "type": "interactive",
                    "title": "SEO Pillars",
                    "content": {
                        "interaction_type": "tabs",
                        "instructions": "Explore the three pillars of SEO.",
                        "completion_condition": "all_tabs_visited",
                        "tabs": [
                            {
                                "id": "dmt1",
                                "label": "Technical SEO",
                                "html": "<h3>Technical SEO</h3><ul><li>Page load speed (Core Web Vitals)</li><li>Mobile-friendly design</li><li>HTTPS / SSL certificate</li><li>XML sitemap &amp; robots.txt</li></ul>"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "dmt2",
                                "label": "On-Page SEO",
                                "html": "<h3>On-Page SEO</h3><ul><li>Keyword research &amp; placement</li><li>Title tags &amp; meta descriptions</li><li>Header tags (H1, H2, H3)</li><li>Internal linking strategy</li></ul>"
                            },
                            {
                                "id": "dmt3",
                                "label": "Off-Page SEO",
                                "html": "<h3>Off-Page SEO</h3><ul><li>Backlinks from authoritative sites</li><li>Social signals</li><li>Brand mentions</li><li>Guest blogging</li></ul>"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "dm-s03",
                    "order": 3,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Content Strategy",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Content Marketing Strategy</h2><p>Great content answers your audience questions and builds trust.</p><ol><li><strong>Identify your audience</strong> — demographics, pain points</li><li><strong>Keyword research</strong> — what are they searching for?</li><li><strong>Content calendar</strong> — consistent publishing schedule</li><li><strong>Formats</strong> — blog posts, videos, infographics, podcasts</li><li><strong>Measure</strong> — traffic, bounce rate, conversions</li></ol>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "unit-dm-02",
            "title": "Module 2: Social Media & Email",
            "order": 2,
            "slides": [
                {
                    "id": "dm-s04",
                    "order": 1,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Social Media Marketing",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Social Media Marketing</h2><p>Choose platforms where your audience lives:</p><ul><li><strong>Facebook / Instagram</strong> — visual content, B2C, broad audiences</li><li><strong>LinkedIn</strong> — B2B, professional networking</li><li><strong>TikTok / Reels</strong> — short video, Gen Z, viral potential</li><li><strong>Twitter/X</strong> — news, real-time, thought leadership</li></ul><p>Key metrics: <em>reach, engagement rate, click-through rate (CTR)</em>.</p>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "id": "dm-s05",
                    "order": 2,
                    "type": "html",
                    "title": "Email Marketing",
                    "content": {
                        "html": "<h2>Email Marketing</h2><p>Email delivers <strong>$42 ROI for every $1 spent</strong> — highest of any channel.</p><ol><li>Build your list organically (opt-ins, lead magnets)</li><li>Segment subscribers by behavior/interest</li><li>Write compelling subject lines (30–50 chars)</li><li>Clear single CTA per email</li><li>A/B test subject lines and send times</li></ol>",
                        "layout": "default"
                    }
                },
